website_summaries.verdict: High quality brand of organic catnip that's sourced from the United States.
pros: Uses both flower tops and leaves for the maximum potency
Ships in a plastic tub to maintain a high level of freshness between uses
Only accepts catnip from safe sources
Even older, picky cats like the flavor and smell
cons: Consistency from package to package isn't always the same

customer_reviews.title: This last tub couldn’t possibly be Yeowww
customer_reviews.text: I’ve bought Yeowww catnip tubs and toys for several years. My cats have always loved it. This last order wasn’t even in a Yeowww tub. It was a plain tub like you get at a grocery deli with a small labelmaker label. It doesn’t look or smell like catnip. They have a carpeted play area and took one sniff and walked away. If they’re trying to make a profit using cheap catnip (if it’s even catnip) they’re not going to get it past the best quality control, as in the CATS!!!
customer_reviews.author: Chiisai

customer_reviews.title: There were multiple large pieces of wood (or stem) in my 2oz tub
customer_reviews.text: Before purchasing this product I had read a review from someone who had purchased this catnip and ended up at the vet due to a stem getting stuck in their kitty’s mouth. So, once I received it I immediately took a look. Within my first handful I found all of these large pieces of wood or stem—any of which could have been horrible if I would have given it to my cats without looking. If you are going to purchase this product be aware and look through it carefully!!!
customer_reviews.author: L

customer_reviews.title: What a waste of money!
customer_reviews.text: I ordered this because my cats went wild over the catnip banana. I have 18 cats so this was more affordable than 18 bananas. Not to mention that the banana split at the seam after only 10 minutes. Anyways, I got this loose nip and put it in socks and squished it really good to get the nip nice end activated and nothing. Nobody reacted to it. Yet if I bring out that poor banana, they are crying and yowling for it. What’s the difference Yeowww?
customer_reviews.author: Tina

customer_reviews.title: Harry loves it!
customer_reviews.text: Our cat went bonkers for the 'nip. After transferring the herb into another container, I gave Harry the empty container to examine, and he started to bite it, and tried to wear it by shoving his whole head into it. This went on for quite a while, until he licked every bit of the 'nip dust out. Then he went to sleep it off for an hour. Good times... All in all, potent catnip, nicely ground (no sticks!), well priced, and very reasonable shipping cost. Will repurchase.
customer_reviews.author: Joanna

customer_reviews.title: Not good.
customer_reviews.text: Bought this a few months ago and my cats LOVED it. Bought it last week - got an unlabeled tub filled with dried plant material that didn't smell at all of catnip. Cats didn't engage when I gave them it. The lack of a label makes me think it may be a fake.
customer_reviews.author: J. Yagid

customer_reviews.title: My cats are hooked!
customer_reviews.text: I've bought two tubs of this stuff. My cats adore it, especially my Shi. The tubs are amazing to, in that when it gets low enough, I "steep" toys in it. After a couple days, I take the toy out and it is infused with catnip scent and my cats again go nuts. Great way of reviving old catnip stuffed toys! The best part for me, though, is the texture. There are no hard bits in this, so I don't have to worry about it hurting my fur babies.
customer_reviews.author: Maria

customer_reviews.title: It works
customer_reviews.text: This catnip is so strong that my cats went nuts before I could open the box that it was shipped in. We have 2 cats 1 loves this stuff the other one loved the box. It is great catnip.
customer_reviews.author: Ginger White

customer_reviews.title: Too much for too little
customer_reviews.text: I had to order 3 containers of catnip minimum because of the weight of the product (2 oz each container). I guess it is the only way the seller would make any money out of it and it is a shame because the product has either lost its scent or it is old. Cats totally uninterested in this catnip. Plus it would take a lifetime to go through 6 oz of catnip. Maybe selling a tub combined with something else that would add weight would help the seller (toy, scratching post for example).
customer_reviews.author: yla

customer_reviews.title: Lots of stems and hard bits
customer_reviews.text: Agree with the other recent reviews that this catnip is not what it use to be and definitely not worth the money. Mine did come in packaging as pictured but it's full of hard stems and rough pieces. I worry as my cat just inhales catnip so there is some danger of him choking on a stem. Shame as this product use to be the best catnip around, but definitely avoid this item that is currently being sold.
customer_reviews.author: sweet_chai

customer_reviews.title: ONE WHIFF AND MY TWO CATS WALKED AWAY!
customer_reviews.text: My cats rate this one star. They took one sniff at the open container and walked away. I'm mystified because this product received rave reviews. But . . . we all know cats are finicky creatures. They like what they .ike and if they don't like it, they will avoid it. The catnip is very finely ground and is green in color. It has an odor like tea leaves and seems very fresh. It came in a clear plastic tub with no graphics like shown in the advertisement. There was only a white label on top with a bar code and "Yeowww catnip" written on the label.
customer_reviews.author: Mac  HenryTop Contributor: Scrapbooking

customer_reviews.title: NOT YEOWWWW
customer_reviews.text: not sure what this dust is, but my cats are all NO..... I've purchased YEOWWW catnip from CHEWY and my kitties loved it almost as much as meowijuana so I want to make sure I am clear, YEOWWW catnip is great - I am not sure what this nip is but I concur with my cats, it's definitely not YEOWWW. Packaging is plain and has zero branding.... I know what the brand is supposed to look like, so I think this is counterfeit
customer_reviews.author: Luxor

customer_reviews.title: This stuff is so great I wish they made it for humans.
customer_reviews.text: Meow! All I can say is watching one feral cat immediately take to Yeowww catnip and seeing the other, more reserved feral cat, take to it in a short amount of time has been an absolute delight. These are hard working barn cats who are not used to taking time for recreation and play. After trying a couple brands with no luck it brought a smile to see them roll around in Yeowww catnip and then jump up and run around playing with one another. I love the sight of them completely covered in catnip acting like kittens kicking back for a little leisure time.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: Didn't seem fresh
customer_reviews.text: I purchased this because my cats love the yeoww banana, so I had thought their brand of catnip would be a good choice. However this did not seem to be a fresh herb at all. Both cats completely ignored it even when placed directly in front of them, and one of my cats is a catnip fiend! I also tried marinating several toys in this for a period of about two weeks. There was no extra interest in the toys once they came out of the catnip. Yet they both still love that damn banana, lol! I want to get whatever kind of catnip it is stuffed with because that is definitely a winner.
customer_reviews.author: JaiPhxDuv

customer_reviews.title: Nicely packaged but no scent
customer_reviews.text: This product has no discernable cat nip scent to it. And, neither of my cats has any reaction to it, or interest in it. Therefore, it gets a one star review. It is advertised as being so great. Maybe it is just my cats, I don't know. I took a chance on it after reading some of the more positive reviews. I don't think there is much zing to it because I normally react badly to catnip and I've had no reaction to this product.
customer_reviews.author: YL

customer_reviews.title: My cat does not like this
customer_reviews.text: All I know is that I had some catnip that my kitty really enjoyed. When it ran out, I bought this catnip. She tried it twice with not much response and now she won’t even get close enough to smell it. And there are a lot of wood shards in it also that I don’t like. I’m going to go back to the old stuff. UPDATE: I went back to our old brand. It took her a minute to try it, but once she did, she loved it!
customer_reviews.author: Marykayeee

customer_reviews.title: Made my cat go to the ER!
customer_reviews.text: My poor baby had a terrible allergic reaction to this product! After carefully reviewing the ingredients and the reviews I bought it so excited my kitty would get more of his favorite thing in the world, catnip! (Besides lovings of course) to my disbelief and horror my poor baby swelled up like a balloon! I had to take him immediately to the emergency vet and get him help. Do not buy this product. I always give my kitty organic stuff. This. This is not a product or a brand I will ever buy from again.
customer_reviews.author: Jenn

customer_reviews.title: No reaction here
customer_reviews.text: Our cat reacts wildly to the Yeowww banana toy, but he had no reaction to this catnip. We tried the suggested sock, putting it out on a towel, etc. Nothing. But the banana toy - oh, my word! Does that get a reaction. It's used as a face pillow and a licking recipient - don't ask, we don't know what's that about. But he does adore his Yeowww bananas.
customer_reviews.author: BMac

customer_reviews.title: Sharp stems not safe for cats
customer_reviews.text: Don't give this to your cats without removing the very sharp stems. As another reviewer pointed out, there are tons of tiny pieces of very sharp stems that aren't safe for cats to eat. It's bad enough that when I grab some of the cat nip out with my fingers, I'll get poked by these little pieces. If it weren't for the stems I would give this product about 2-3 stars. It's generally low quality with tons of seeds and stems, but the cats do react to it and seem to like it.
customer_reviews.author: Brian

customer_reviews.title: My cat loves it
customer_reviews.text: My cat is very picky about catnip, she doesn't go crazy for it like other cats, but she likes to eat it and sit on it. Cats. But, the Yeowww actually made her have a little party. She rolled around on it, scratched at it, ate it, and had a good time. This is the only catnip she's ever responded to like that. I think that means this must be the good stuff. I like that it appears to be mostly buds and leaves, it smells nice and fresh if you roll it between your fingers, and I didn't encounter any sharp stems or sticks at all.
customer_reviews.author: Nina L

customer_reviews.title: Not fresh
customer_reviews.text: Seemed like old stock. My cats and I both agree that this catnip was very old or very poor quality. I grow my own catnip for all my furry friends so I know what good, fresh catnip smells like. Unfortunately our backyard harvest wasn't that good this year due to moving to a new planting bed. I didn't produce enough to last the whole Winter and that's why I had to purchase this tub. Looking forward to next year's crop as it should be huge as the bed will be more established.
customer_reviews.author: Tom S.

customer_reviews.title: Spent - Should have returned
customer_reviews.text: If my cat could chew me out, kick me in the pants and yell at me, she would say "Why would you think I wanted a QP of seeds and stems???!!!!" I sprinkled a bit of this on her bed, she looked up, her eyes said - 'honey - puhleez' and dissed me like only a cat could. This isn't good catnip, really was a waste of money and the plastic in which was recycled. Find another brand.
customer_reviews.author: Josh Peller

customer_reviews.title: This nip is potent! My cats could smell it ...
customer_reviews.text: This nip is potent! My cats could smell it through the tub and have gotten weirder on it than I've ever seen them. Even my fat, lazy Rose went crazy tearing up and down the hallway on this. No sticks or sharp bits in here either. I have been making cat toys for the local shelter and I only need a pinch of nip in each toy.
customer_reviews.author: Kayla

customer_reviews.title: Kitty gives four paws up
customer_reviews.text: I researched the highest rated catnip. This was at the top of several sites. It has lived up to the ratings. More actual plant in this brand than most, which means more actual fun for the kitty. Very few seeds and stalks. He loves his catnip parties, especially with Yeowww brand. I store it in the freezer to help the catnip smell last longer.
customer_reviews.author: Becky A

customer_reviews.title: Better than most, but not the best
customer_reviews.text: Most of my cats liked this brand, but one of them would have nothing to do with it. He definitely loves catnip, just not this brand. My other three cats loved it though-eating, licking and rolling in it. The directions say to put a handful into a sock, give it a squeeze to release the oils/scent and give it to them to play with. In the past, my cats ignored toys like this. They prefer a small pile in the floor that they can either start eating or roll around in and then lick it off themselves.
customer_reviews.author: Chris

customer_reviews.title: Yeee-ouch! New formula pokes, be advised.
customer_reviews.text: Both cats turned away and now I have a big bucket they won’t use. I bought the large version because they loved this brand before (small bucket from local per store), but they seem to have changed their formula. The catnip I had before was very fine (almost powder) and now it has big clumps and is VERY coarse. Disappointed in the new mix.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: bad batch???
customer_reviews.text: I don't know. I have 3 cats. None of the cats give this catnip the time of day. They watch me put it out on their favorite things (scratching posts, mats, beds). They walk over and take a sniff. And then all 3 of them move on as if it smells like nothing. Is it too old? I cannot say for sure, but I am extremely disappointed, especially given the size of the huge tub. Bummer.
customer_reviews.author: ajc2016Phila

customer_reviews.title: FAKE!!!
customer_reviews.text: I've bought this brand many times before and it WAS a premium product. Container and label look FAKE. Color of the catnip in the picture is GREEN. Color of the fake (or low quality) catnip is BROWN. I will not trust AMAZON (the stated seller) again with this product.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: Best Brand Catnip I Have Ever Purchased!
customer_reviews.text: Yeowww!!! makes great cat toys (Banana, Cigar etc). Our cats have always liked that brand cat toy the best. I bought this cat nip and put it in a zip loc baggie and put some of my cat’s toys in there for a couple of days. Old toys were suddenly as favored as his new ones. Walk into my house and you would think that I have a toddler with all the toys all over, except my “toddler” walks on four legs. I think that the “Yeowww!!!” Catnip is the best I have ever purchased.
customer_reviews.author: Nancy B.

customer_reviews.title: Catnip of choice for my pickiest cat, but still some minor small stems, but I will blender them.
customer_reviews.text: I feed a male feral kitty and he has enjoyed all the brands of catnip... However, my spoiled female kitty has turned up her nose to ALL cat nip except this one... She cannot resist this one. So I'm pleased with her stamp-of-approval with this brand!! The only down side is that there are some small stems that I pick out. It's better than the other brands, but I'm afraid of the sticks pricking their mouths. Next time, I'm putting this catnip in the blender to shred the stems. I'm not sure there are any brands that do not have some stems. My kitties are pleased with this product.
customer_reviews.author: Christina N

customer_reviews.title: Strong nip for delighted kitties!
customer_reviews.text: I bought several tubs of this to make catnip toys for Christmas. It is just like the catnip they use in their own Yeow toys that have been uber popular with my cats. The catnip is potent and strong smelling. It was a challenge making my crafts and keeping my cats away! In the end I had to give them some to play with to distract them from my project! I highly recommend this product if your cats like catnip and you want to use this to make your own toys, refresh existing toys or spread onto a cat scratcher. Its strong scent will delight your kitties.
customer_reviews.author: AFox

customer_reviews.text: MAMA BOUGHT ME THIS CATNIP. I LOVE THIS CATNIP. SHE HAD TO DRAG ME OUT OF THE TUB THE FIRST TIME SHE OPENED IT. ALL IT TAKES IS A LITTLE BIT TO MAKE ME GO NUTS. I SAY IT TAKES MORE, BUT SHE REFUSES TO GIVE ME MORE! PACKAGE IS TOO HARD FOR KITTENS TO GET INTO, WHICH IS UNFAIR. IT SMELLS JUST LIKE THE FRESH LEAVES SHE BRINGS ME FROM THE GARDEN. 10/10, TWO PAWS UP, MAMA BETTER BUY ME MORE WHEN THIS GIANT TUB RUNS OUT!!
customer_reviews.author: Kat

customer_reviews.title: Catnip Addiction is real
customer_reviews.text: Mr. Schmelly Cat, my partner's cat-child and my adopted cat child is completely enamored with this particular brand of nip. He wallowed in it for about 30 minutes, ran around like a maniac, chewed stuff up, was high enough to keep rolling out of his cat bed. He slept like a baby afterward. It's good stuff. I have to keep it in the fridge or else he would tear the container up trying to get more. I admit, he has a nip problem. but this is quality stuff.
customer_reviews.author: Jane's Most Wanted

customer_reviews.title: A miss except for a senior cat
customer_reviews.text: It smells like catnip and despite their banana and cigar toys being a hit, this is a miss. Foster mom of currently 7 cats with the youngest at 3 years, oldest at 14. Six of them have ignored it, the oldest actually has rubbed his paws in and has licked it. Too many stems and not as green as I would have liked.
customer_reviews.author: CaroCat

customer_reviews.title: I think I got a Dud
customer_reviews.text: I've bought Yeowww catnip Bananas before, and some my cat just loved for weeks, and some not as long -- but it always got some reaction when it was first given to her. I just figured that some were fresher. So, I decided to try this Catnip Tub and filled a sock as suggested on the package with 1/2 the tub. Gave it to my cat and got no reaction at all. Let her smell the tub -- not interested. Maybe it's old? In short, didn't work at all, which was a first for her.
customer_reviews.author: Gregory J. Jansen

customer_reviews.title: Cats are not a fan
customer_reviews.text: I usually have good luck with Yeowww products, their catnip cigars are some of my kitty’s favorite toys, but they did not like this. It smells very different than the toys, more of a weedy smell. It not only did nothing for my cats, they were actively repulsed by it!
customer_reviews.author: CAT

customer_reviews.title: Great even for “proper” cats. :)
customer_reviews.text: Great product for the best price. I have 2 cats, 1 is hype to the traditional “nip” while the other couldn’t care less. However, this blend stimulates them both and they can’t get enough! Mind you, I only treat them with a very small amount sparingly because it is incredibly strong. The one cat fell off their cat tree while the other one (though safe and pleased) began excessively drooling.
customer_reviews.author: Gabby

customer_reviews.title: My cat had a good time!
customer_reviews.text: My cat looooves it! I was a little worried bc previously I’ve gotten her the catnip with silvervine (which i think she still prefers) but she still had a great time with this. And you really do get a lot for the money and the tub is quite convenient for dispensing Ps the video I included was originally a live picture but I turned it into a video so I could post it to show my cat enjoying the ‘nip
customer_reviews.author: Chasepants

customer_reviews.title: Mild vs. Potent
customer_reviews.text: ☆☆☆If you're looking for something more potent, this isn't the nip you need. Although, perhaps your fur baby prefers something mild. THIS IS YOUR NIP.
customer_reviews.author: Sheila

customer_reviews.title: My cats love this.
customer_reviews.text: I take care of my neighborhood cat colony. It has taken 3 years, but my husband and I have caught and vetted 30 cats. I use this catnip in a mixture that I make with a couple other brands. Catnip, cat cookies and tuna are very important around my house.
customer_reviews.author: Megan

customer_reviews.title: ... for all the cat lovers in my family and love to get the feed back of cats slobbering over ...
customer_reviews.text: I make catnip toys for all the cat lovers in my family and love to get the feed back of cats slobbering over their new toy or other interesting stories. Some people send me pictures of their cats mauling the new toy. They say they have never had catnip work like Yeow does. I know, I have eleven to keep happy. Thanks for the great product.
customer_reviews.author: 2Dinah

customer_reviews.title: Cat could not care less about this.
customer_reviews.text: Video speaks for itself, cat was simply not interested after checking it out.
customer_reviews.author: Jason

customer_reviews.title: My kittie goes bonkers over this stuff!
customer_reviews.text: Yeoww is right! I’ve had cats my entire life, which is over 50years now. I’ve grown my own cat nip and I have purchased lots of it. This brand is incredible! All I have to do is lift the lid on the catnip tub, and my kitty’s eyes roll back in her head, she flops on her back, and playtime is on!!! This is the best catnip I’ve ever used. My sister’s cat doesn’t respond to catnip, so I gave her some of mine in a baggie to take hope to her kitty. I got a call from her telling me her cat was going nuts over it! I’ll only use this stuff from now on!
customer_reviews.author: TrishRN

customer_reviews.title: Not strong nip, bad packaging.
customer_reviews.text: Leaf is green looks fresh, but cats are less interested in this than the catnip can I had from target that was a year old. They roll all over the old stuff. Love it. Only 1 cat is interested in this can, and it’s only a mild interest. Packaging allowed a lot of leaf to fall out. (Soft can shipped in a bag, so when crushed lid came off enough to let contents out. threw out about 15% of product due to crap packaging. Won’t but again. We’ve gone through lots of catnip, this stuff is not great. Considering returning.
customer_reviews.author: Sandbags

customer_reviews.title: For the Cats
customer_reviews.text: The fourteen cats who have benefited so far from the catnip pillows they received for Christmas have offered a 100% happiness rating for the quality and strength of this catnip. Two were hard core catnip lovers who now sleep and rub on their new pillows. Two were younger and hadn't been around catnip before. They have it down now, and love it too. This catnip is strong and seems fresh. There is a lot of it in the 3 tubs. It's a good product I will order again.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: Lots of Stems but
customer_reviews.text: ...as soon as I took the container out of the shipping envelope one of my cats stood up and came after it. Then another cat from another room came running in. Then my 3rd cat who was hanging out outside came running in! I had no idea they had such a strong sense of smell. I hadn't even broke the plastic seal on it yet! Anyway, I sprinkled it in different locations and only my 3rd cat persisted in playing in it (actually lied down so firmly his body flattened out).
customer_reviews.author: Katherine & Dave

customer_reviews.title: My nip-head cat's say, "It's just OK"
customer_reviews.text: Neither of my cats are particularly enthusiastic about this brand's product, though they are crazy about another one.
customer_reviews.author: Theo

customer_reviews.title: Loyal customer
customer_reviews.text: My cats favorite brand of catnip! In the past I’ve tried different brands of catnip. Some made my cat threw up and made him feel not so good, some came with too many dangerous looking branches. But yeoww is my cats favorite without all the problems other brands had! It chills him out and he seems to enjoy the flavor very much <33 loyal customer for going on 9years ;)
customer_reviews.author: Myumbella

customer_reviews.title: Good product could be packed better.
customer_reviews.text: Badly packed, the container was cracked. The catnip was coming out into the shipping package. I was able to transfer a good amount without too much loss. My cat was extremely pleased with it. Looked nice and fresh.
customer_reviews.author: Ashes Bijoux

customer_reviews.title: Don't Buy!!!
customer_reviews.text: Couldn't wait to give my cats a treat. They were all excited when I bought the container out. Upon giving them each a couple sprinkles on their favorite toys, they took one sniff and walked away like I was playing a joke on them. Might as well have been sawdust! Tried a few more times and even gave some to friends for their cats. Same unhappy response. Don't know if this product is old or what, but totally Not worth it!!!
customer_reviews.author: Margaret Anne Ebling

customer_reviews.title: Steer Clear
customer_reviews.text: I buy those off the rack catnip toys and my cat turns into an idiot. So I see great reviews of "YEOWWW!" so I get some. Nothing. Might as well be a handful of week old lawn clippings.
customer_reviews.author: Bob Maguire

customer_reviews.title: have fun. This is awesome stuff
customer_reviews.text: Only fines, no sticks and remarkably potent. The cats are both losing their minds. When they don't have access to it they will open doors, pick locks, tunnel underground to get at the container. So, buyer beware? But for realsies, have fun. This is awesome stuff.
customer_reviews.author: Aaron

customer_reviews.title: My cat didn't care :-(
customer_reviews.text: My cat LOVED her Yeowww brand banana toy, but stopped playing with it after a while, I thought because the catnip scent faded. I bought this to "refresh" her toys and spread on her scratcher etc. She did not care at ALL. Literally no response. I was surprised and bummed. :-( Two stars because the catnip seemed to have a scent to me, it felt soft-ish rather than super scratchy, and it was a full container. Ah well, cats are weird!
customer_reviews.author: Kassie and Alex

customer_reviews.title: No label, not sealed
customer_reviews.text: This is my 3rd time ordering this particular catnip and for some reason, this batch came without any yeow label nor was it sealed like the others. Before I gave it to my cats, I smelled it and checked it thoroughly to make sure it wasn’t some strange mixture. I am sure it is catnip. But this is poor product representation. I would have returned it, but it’s more than it’s worth. And my cats seem fine after partaking in it. No side effects.
customer_reviews.author: Charlene

customer_reviews.title: Dried out/old
customer_reviews.text: I’m rating this poorly because my tub of catnip arrived cracked open and the catnip spilled everywhere in the packaging. It was also dried out and very old. Both of my cats took one sniff and walked away. They loved the catnip bananas from this brand so I figured I’d a buy an entire tub. What a waste of money. They should do quality control on their stock from time to time.
customer_reviews.author: Kendall

customer_reviews.title: Wow! Zing! Pow! This is the drug of choice for cats.
customer_reviews.text: By far this is the best dried cat pinup I have ever purchased. It is fragrant and utterly irresistible to cats. I've used it to calm rescues and in humane traps to catch the Tomcats responsible for most of the unwanted kittens in my neighborhood. Even the most wily old Tom could not resist this stuff! And naturally, our foster cats love it too. It really helps calm them in this new environment while they wait for a permanent home.
customer_reviews.author: Spud's PlaceTop Contributor: Pets

customer_reviews.title: works great and is a great value
customer_reviews.text: I am very happy this catnip. It is very effective and a super good deal. I use it to make a solution to spray instead of using store-bought sprays, which i noticed didn't work well. And this solution works great. I also sprinkle the dry form in the litter boxes. My cats all have the gene, and they all respond very well to this catnip. I agree with what other reviewers have said about its containing very few stems.
customer_reviews.author: User2

customer_reviews.title: Open package carefully.
customer_reviews.text: My cat seems to like the smell. Do not open this package anywhere you don't want catnip spread around. The container is a light weight plastic tub..... it was shipped in a bubble-bag...... it did not survive the passage from store to door. Be prepared to have a zip lock bag handy for what remains.
customer_reviews.author: Trebor 2

customer_reviews.title: They love it!
customer_reviews.text: I just kinda grab some and grind it up in my hand while sprinkling it out for them. They love it and eat it all! Then get all frisky lol... I recommend this for your fur babies!
customer_reviews.author: Amy Cross

customer_reviews.title: Lasts a. long time
customer_reviews.text: I bought a tub in 2018 and put it in a cupboard Forgot it... For a year or so. Pulled out recently recently scattered it around. The cats went bonkers, especially the one that got the lid off and did his own scattering. Have cats that are happy excercised and intoxictexy. Still potent, good stuff.
customer_reviews.author: Not too old

customer_reviews.title: Cat is not interested
customer_reviews.text: My cat is not interested at all. I'm going to try and grow my own as in years passed I've grown it and my cat at that time was nutso for it. Literally ate it down to dirt level and was very, very happy.
customer_reviews.author: Dane

customer_reviews.title: My cat is obsessed.
customer_reviews.text: I bought this because everytime I would buy a "Stinky" from Yeowww my cat would immediately start chewing it up trying to get to the catnip. I bought this and now he's obsessed. I have a toy if his I add it to and when he's low/out, he definitely let's me know. A definite staple of cat supplies!
customer_reviews.author: Myranda Z.

customer_reviews.title: Is there crack in this ‘nip?
customer_reviews.text: Never seen my cat react so much to catnip before. She goes bonkers and we have a blast. She has developed a ‘nip habit and starts howling for it every night around 9pm. Gets her ‘nip and then we play for 30 min, so that she doesn’t wake me up with psycho zoomies and biting my nose at 3:30AM
customer_reviews.author: Lalala

customer_reviews.title: My kitty has been partying for hours off and on....
customer_reviews.text: In all fairness, my kitty loves even the cheapest catnip, but one whiff of this stuff made her crazy! She tried to rip it right out of my hands, as she meowed loudly (she's usually not very vocal) So I guess I have to take her word for it and give this kitty weed 5 stars.
customer_reviews.author: VJErwood

customer_reviews.title: Not my cats favorite
customer_reviews.text: Cat doesn't enjoy this as much as the other products in amazon.
customer_reviews.author: Steel Sarj

customer_reviews.title: packs a punch!
customer_reviews.text: if you dont have alot of money to spend or want to have alot of catnip around this really will do it! it had a cat that never liked nip BEFORE totally in love with it!!we're talking rolling it, eating it, moaning & just drooling with it!! it really packs a punch!
customer_reviews.author: Jan

customer_reviews.title: Cats love it. Container tricky to open
customer_reviews.text: I have bought this product many times. Scent is always good, stays fresh until the bottom of the jar, and the cats love it. The lid is tricky to open, especially when the jar is full. It's easy to spill some on you. Just makes your cats love you more.
customer_reviews.author: SGBELVERTA

customer_reviews.title: ALL I CAN SAY IS WOW!
customer_reviews.text: This stuff is the real deal! My cats go absolutely nuts when given this catnip. This is very fresh and potent catnip! You can't beat the price for this large quantity and super quality! I will never consider the purchase another brand of catnip, not ever! This is what your kitties are looking for!
customer_reviews.author: Al Einstein

customer_reviews.title: The one!
customer_reviews.text: My cat Cesar loves this catnip! He rolls around in it then eats it, I am very pleased that he responded so well to this product. Others that I tried were a big waste for he would just either snub it or walk away in a huff! Thank you for making a wonderful product!
customer_reviews.author: Via A Baltus

customer_reviews.title: Potent.
customer_reviews.text: This was a Christmas present for our cats. I put it in their stocking and they attacked it that night. I thought it’s sealed in a plastic container with plastic wrap should be good. NO.... great product cats love love it. Better than any in the store.
customer_reviews.author: phyllis carter

customer_reviews.title: Fairly potent
customer_reviews.text: My two cats like it. It costs more than other brands, but it's better in two ways: 1) It's a small container, which helps keep the catnip potent; 2) it has fewer stem bits and more leaves than other brands (more potent and fewer splinters).
customer_reviews.author: J

customer_reviews.title: Biting the box and container to get in!
customer_reviews.text: Found out it was delivered when my male cat was biting the box at the door. Brought it in and my female cat was playing with the unsealed tub. My dog wondered what it was, too. I'd say it's potent. Not as green as in the photo, but they're certainly interested in it.
customer_reviews.author: Mike

customer_reviews.title: This is like super awesome catnip.
customer_reviews.text: My cat loses his stuff over this! A little goes a long way! I gave half the tub to a friend and her cat loves it too! It's a great price and it's cheaper than the stuff you get in the store. Plus you get more. Will be buying this from now on.
customer_reviews.author: Nikki

customer_reviews.title: Great catnip
customer_reviews.text: Made catnip booties for Christmas for all my cat friends. Very fragrant and much loved. Will have to do anther batch. Used cat covers for bottom of chair legs also purchased thru Amazon. Inset catnip and sew closed. Piece of cake.
customer_reviews.author: Adirondack Nana

customer_reviews.title: My cats aren't into it this at all
customer_reviews.text: After reading a lot of reviews I bought this figuring with so many positive reviews that my cats would love this stuff. Nope, not at all. They prefer some really basic catnip over this brand. It might be a good brand for other cats, but not mine. Not disappointed, live and learn right..
customer_reviews.author: Flint Jamenson

customer_reviews.title: Best cat nip
customer_reviews.text: Found out about this from using it in the clinic I work at, and I'm so glad. It smells so sweet I almost want to make tea with it, if I was ok with depriving my cats. They love it so much, they keep trying to crack the tub open!!
customer_reviews.author: AriaRei

customer_reviews.title: The picture is not correct.  This is the smaller tub, not the tall one pictured.
customer_reviews.text: My cats are so high, they'll be high till tomorrow. Best catnip available IMHO. Smells almost like weed it's soo strong.
customer_reviews.author: d3bug

customer_reviews.title: Potent & fresh
customer_reviews.text: The cat loves it. I put a tablespoon on a clean towel. She licks it off the towel. This catnip is so good that the aroma on the towel keeps her happy for a couple of days. I only give her a catnip treat once a week so she stays very excited.
customer_reviews.author: Rochelle Fogg

customer_reviews.title: YOU CALL THIS CATNIP? HOW OLD IS THIS STUFF?
customer_reviews.text: GAVE IT TO MY CAT, VERY UNINPRESSIVE. SNIFFED THE STUF, AND THAT WAS ABOUT ALL. I RECOMEND KONG BRAND CATNIP. WORKS ALL THE TIME.
customer_reviews.author: Robin tim mAmazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: No interest
customer_reviews.text: Cat did not react to this catnip in any way. Took a sniff and walked away.
customer_reviews.author: Natalie

customer_reviews.title: Potent Catnip!
customer_reviews.text: I had merely opened the tub and my cat came charging. He was meowing loudly as I stuffed a sock with the catnip. He spent the night rubbing, biting, and clawing the infused sock, then fell asleep. He absolutely loves it.
customer_reviews.author: Steven Byrd

customer_reviews.title: Yeowwww brings them meowing.
customer_reviews.text: The Yeowww catnip is a better catnip than many others. Our 2 cats love it
customer_reviews.author: Mari G. H.

customer_reviews.title: Purrfection!  Best catnip ever
customer_reviews.text: I have been buying this catnip for years, and I love that it’s organic. I don’t want my babies munching on, and eating catnip with pesticides. And they love it. Yeowww! is always potent. And their catnip toys are excellent too.
customer_reviews.author: Sniggih

customer_reviews.title: Not the ultimate cat nip
customer_reviews.text: If my cats could talk they’d say this is meh! No extreme reactions. It hardly smelled like cat nip, and for this price it should have. It actually smelled like old cat nip. I give it to them because I paid for it and I’m not just going to throw it in the garbage, but they clearly aren’t crazy about it.
customer_reviews.author: Elizabeth L.

customer_reviews.title: Good catnip
customer_reviews.text: The catnip is good but the container is not. It is hard to open and i doubt it seals very good. I moved it into a screw top container.
customer_reviews.author: Bruce

customer_reviews.title: Fresh and almost no stems
customer_reviews.text: My cats LOVE this brand. They run to the tub every time I open it. Whereas other brands I’ve purchased in the past, they turned their noses on. The cats don’t lie. I will be sure to buy this brand from this seller again in the future.
customer_reviews.author: Mars Baby

customer_reviews.title: Not up to snuff??
customer_reviews.text: My cat loves Catnip. For some reason, she’s not crazy about this brand. Perhaps the smell is not strong enough? I don’t know and she’s not talking.
customer_reviews.author: nottoca

customer_reviews.title: My cats love Yeowww and the tub is a good value
customer_reviews.text: Yeowww products are a favorite with me and my cats. They like to get high, I like to watch. This stuff is super potent. I sprinkle it on the rug, or tie up an old sock with some of this in there, and just watch the kitty chaos ensue. I like the tub more than the cloth Yeowww toys because you get more for your money, and my cat spit tends to make the toys get smelly and moldy once it gets hot out, so this is a more practical option.
customer_reviews.author: Scarlett

customer_reviews.title: Abby doesn’t like it
customer_reviews.text: My cat likes catnip but this product doesn’t make the grade. Can’t recommend.
customer_reviews.author: Largoann

customer_reviews.title: Cats loved it.
customer_reviews.text: Not sure what to say. This isbgood catnip, and our cats love it.
customer_reviews.author: Individualist

customer_reviews.title: lots of leaves no stems
customer_reviews.text: My two Psycho's love this stuff it induces much needed bursts of energy from the Fat girl and provides the boy with mucho macho West side story finger snapping, gang dancing displays of coolness. He's so involved in his shtick he doesn't even notice the contempt and disdain hurling his way courtesy of the ever entitled center of the universe Miss NESA. But yeah we like it just fine. (eye roll) Good Theatre.
customer_reviews.author: Deborah Samson

customer_reviews.title: Have tried several others, keep coming back to YEOWWW Cat Catnip
customer_reviews.text: My cats continue to show they really like this catnip. I fill a small, old sock with it and they'll play with it and lay on it for a long time. It is well processed with no stems and has a wonderful, strong catnip scent.
customer_reviews.author: V. Waters

customer_reviews.title: Best catnip out there in the opinion of our 7 cats!
customer_reviews.text: I can "marinate" a catnip toy in this that has lost it's appeal, and it is like they get a new toy. This stuff is amazing. This size is a bargain as well. I recommend this to all fellow cat folks!
customer_reviews.author: LWeaver

customer_reviews.title: Kitty goes crazy for this nip
customer_reviews.text: I love the fact that this is reasonably priced, high quality organic nip with very little stems in it. The container is thick and pops in the freezer easily for preserving. As soon as I got this and opened the lid my cat ran over and stuck her head right in it. She seems to love this brand.
customer_reviews.author: Kelly N.

customer_reviews.title: Does not work! Don’t waste your money!
customer_reviews.text: My cat did not even react to it. My cat actually seems to dislike the smell of the product even thought she loves catnip. This product cannot be catnip. Wasted my money. Don’t waste yours.
customer_reviews.author: Natalia Del Valle Catoni

customer_reviews.title: Not recommended
customer_reviews.text: I don’t believe this is real Yeowww! catnip. My cats LOVE the Yeowww! catnip toys and they were all less than impressed with this stuff. It smells nothing like the toys either. The only plus is that I was able to get a refund on my purchase.
customer_reviews.author: Diane Beck

customer_reviews.title: Cats go Crazy for this catnip!!
customer_reviews.text: Love this catnip - both of my cats go crazy for this brand. I store mine in the fridge to keep it fresh. When they hear me pull it out and shake it, they come running! LOL .. great stuff!!
customer_reviews.author: Sassy

customer_reviews.title: Not product as pictured!
customer_reviews.text: Came in a generic container with a label. Is not the same product as I have purchased from other vendors which my cat loves. My cat won't touch it!
customer_reviews.author: Blanco

customer_reviews.title: Not impressed
customer_reviews.text: My cats are normally huge cat nip fans but they don't even react to this cat nip at all, I'm not sure why
customer_reviews.author: Evan Colon

customer_reviews.title: Cat LOVES this!
customer_reviews.text: My cat went bonkers over this catnip!! She is very shy and timid but she spent 30-45mins rolling around playing with her mesh bag filled with this catnip. Great to see her so energized.
customer_reviews.author: minpin08

customer_reviews.title: Didn't work for my cat.
customer_reviews.text: My cat doesn't react to this at all. It was also full of stems. Stems are a choking hazard.
customer_reviews.author: LJ

product_meta.title: Yeowww! Cat Catnip Made in USA
product_meta.description: Size:2 oz. TubStuffed with the same high-grade 100% organically grown catnip that fills our other Yeowww! catnip toys. Available in 2-oz. and 4-oz. tubs, the Yeowww! Catnip Tub™ packs a punch even for the most high-maintenance or older finicky cats.
